Court Rules Credit Suisse Must Release Data, Tages-Anzeiger Says

-- B y   C a r o l y n   B a n d e l
-- 
2011-10-18T05:32:10Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/court-rules-credit-suisse-must-release-data-tages-anzeiger-says.html
Zurich’s cantonal high court ruled
on Oct. 1 that  Credit Suisse Group AG (CSGN)  must give two clients, who
argue the bank lost almost 1 million Swiss francs ($1.1
million) of their investments because of unauthorized risky
options trades, insight into their client data,  Tages-Anzeiger 
reported, citing Oliver Gnehm, the clients’ lawyer.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carolyn Bandel in Zurich at 
 cbandel@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Frank Connelly at 
 fconnelly@bloomberg.net  